  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Many countries have legal requirements for reporting suspicious financial activities that could indicate money laundering. Typically, financial institutions and certain businesses must:\n\n1. Report suspicious transactions to financial intelligence units\n2. Conduct customer due diligence\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Train employees to recognize potential money laundering indicators\n\nHowever, specific details can vary by jurisdiction. I recommend consulting local legal resources for precise requirements.",
